        "created_at": "2025-09-23T04:25:31.088Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Originally I had my desktop linked to my phone. From what I recall it brought in the last 45 days of messaging history. This is also promised in <a href=\"https://signal.org/blog/a-synchronized-start-for-linked-devices/\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">this blog post</a>. That all worked fine.</p>\n<p>Now I changed phones, which required me to switch Signal from the original phone to the new phone. That worked.</p>\n<p>That caused my desktop app to require re-linking. I did that, now it has a gap in message history between when I changed to the new phone until I re-linked the desktop, even though the gap is far less than 45 days (it’s at most a day or two). So when people reply to things I see, “Original message not found.” Even though that message is sitting there on my phone on the same desk.</p>\n<p>Presumably now I have the choice of either:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Deleting all data on Signal desktop, losing all history on my desktop that extends beyond 45 days, then linking anew, getting 45 days of history, fixing the gap</li>\n<li>Leaving it as-is and having this gap</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Is that how this is supposed to work?</p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 6,
