        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/m/4da419/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2025-09-23T05:36:34.082Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Blog post only says 45 days for media. It doesn’t specify for text. Old beta testing threads suggest all text history will be transferred.</p>\n<aside class=\"quote quote-modified\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"65452\">\n  <div class=\"title\">\n    <div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n    <img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/greyson-signal/48/2005_2.png\" class=\"avatar\">\n    <div class=\"quote-title__text-content\">\n      <a href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/t/help-us-test-desktop-history-syncing/65452\">Help us test desktop history syncing!</a> <a class=\"badge-category__wrapper \" href=\"/c/announcements/call-for-testing/96\"><span data-category-id=\"96\" style=\"--category-badge-color: #0088CC; --category-badge-text-color: #FFFFFF; --parent-category-badge-color: #ED207B;\" data-parent-category-id=\"5\" data-drop-close=\"true\" class=\"badge-category --style-square --has-parent\" title=\"Calls for testing by the Signal team (outside of regular Beta Feedback).\"><span class=\"badge-category__name\">Call for Testing</span></span></a>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  <blockquote>\n    Hello, all! Some of you are aware that we’ve been working on a pretty cool device-independent backup format, and now we’re looking to test our first use-case: syncing your message history with a newly-linked device! You heard that right – your newly-linked devices will finally have all of your message history <img width=\"20\" height=\"20\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/images/emoji/apple/tada.png?v=14\" title=\"tada\" alt=\"tada\" class=\"emoji\"> \nI think this is something we’ve all wanted for a while, so it’s really cool to finally build it. But building something like this is very tricky, and testing it tends to uncover lot…\n  </blockquote>\n</aside>\n",
